I purchased this CZ-50 from SOG and I could find no indication that the pistol had been fired since leaving the arsenal. There were no marks on the slide or frame rails, the underside of the slide, the hammer, nor the breech face. I have put 50 rounds through it.  The pictures tell the story of the current condition.  It is a CAI import, manufactured in 1950 with SN 654xxx.

In case you're unfamiliar with the CZ-50, it was the standard Czech police sidearm that was manufactured from 1950 though 1970.  It is all steel construction and was closely copied from the Walther PP.  It is chambered in 7.65 mm (.32 ACP) and employs a blowback mechanism.

Must present government ID showing you are a resident of Ohio of legal age to purchase a handgun.

Serious buyers may request high resolution photographs.

title: For Sale:  Price Drop:  1926 Spanish Mauser w/ Ammo and Bayonet
postcontent:
I picked this Model 1916 Spanish Mauser with the intent on restoring it. It has the Oviedo crest, dated 1926, and Serial numbers on barrel and receiver match. The rear sight is the "roller coast" style, which was only used on this model for one year, and is thus very rare. This rifle is also in the original 7mm chambering.
  The stock is in really good shape, and was refinished with tung oil. The outside of the barrel and several of the metal parts show some pitting in areas. I cleaned off all the rust (which was so significant in places that the rifle was rust-welded into the stock), and cold-blued the barrel and all stripped parts to give some protection. The receiver was not stripped, and had no rust. The trigger group, receiver, magazine follower, and the bolt are in really good shape, and are all-original.  The rifle functions smoothly and flawlessly, and the trigger pull is extremely smooth and crisp.
  The pitting on the barrel is on the outside, right at the wood line. The pitting does not appear to be deep enough to affect safe operation, and is pretty far from the chamber. Speaking of the chamber, there is some throat wear, but the rifling is very strong.
  I have never fired this rifle, so I can't comment on how it shoots. I have 60 rounds of new production reloadable factory ammunition, as well as 35 factory reloads, which are loaded to standard specs, and were given to me by a licensed ammunition manufacturer. I am also including a nice, long bayonet, which mounts up perfectly. The metal has some serious pitting, and there is a repaired crack in the handle. The bayonet is structurally sound, and looks pretty neat when mounted to the gun.
  There are some minor tooling marks on some of the minor hardware, but not much at all: from what I recall, one of the recoil cross bolts has a notch cut into the head for ease of removal, but that doesn't affect functionality.

  Let me know if you want further info, or have any questions, or want more detailed pictures.  Price was dropped to $200.00 FIRM for the lot, which breaks down as $10.00 for the bayonet (which I think is a Model 1917), $40.00 for the 95 rounds of ammo (all brass-cased, boxer primed, and reloadable), and $150.00 for the rifle.  I will not ship, and all I require for the sale is a peek at your GA license, and a generic bill of sale for my records (name, signature, and date only...no personal information like license number or address of anything). We must meet in the Conyers/Covington area.

This pistol is the exact remake of the Beretta-92.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Italian made 92FS 9mm
location: WF / North Raleigh / Franklinton, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent:
92FS: The World’s Most Trusted Military and Police Pistol

The Beretta 92FS has been setting the standards for best military, police and tactical pistol for over a quarter century. The reason is that it was designed--and has kept evolving--to be and remain the most accurate, durable and reliable semiauto handgun on the market. Easy to use, absolutely safe and delivering impressive firepower, it remains the sidearm of the US military and of allied forces the world over, as well as of countless police and law-enforcement agencies.


Superior Reliability

The 92FS is a double/single-action semiauto pistol that employs an open-slide, short-recoil delayed locking-block system, which yields a faster cycle time and delivers exceptional accuracy and reliability. In particular, the open-slide design practically eliminates “stove-piping” and helps flawless cycling and feeding even after thousands and thousands of rounds. The recently-renewed contract with the US military speaks clear: when it comes to dependability even in some of the world’s most extreme conditions, the Beretta 92FS still has no match. Period.     


Match-Grade Accuracy out of the Box

Regardless of the wonderful reputation it may have, the true test for a tactical pistol’s worth is at the shooting range. The 92FS consistently bests the US military requirement of a 10-shot group of 3” or less at 50 meters (just short of 55 yards). While this type of  match-grade accuracy is impressive, it is no magic. At Beretta, we know that absolutely precise tolerances keep performance consistent shot after shot—which not only gives the 92FS its extraordinary accuracy, but it makes all factory parts interchangeable within the same model. Couple this to the ability to reliably feed every variety of commercial ammunition, and it is easy to understand why the 92FS remains the best pistol in its class.


Packed with Useful Tactical Features

This pistol offers a variety of tactical features that make it equally safe, easy to use and dependable in the holster of military personnel as well as for home or personal defense. Its reversible magazine release lets you use either hand for tactical magazine changes, while its ambidextrous safety-decocker makes it flexible for right- or left-handed persons or for shooters trying out different gripping or shooting styles. Its Bruniton finish is highly resistant to sweat and corrosion, and after shooting, a tool-free disassembly latch makes it a snap to take the pistol apart for cleaning. These and countless other useful features make the 92FS the choice of military and police professionals all over the world, as well as individuals wanting the absolute best for sport or self-protection.
